Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{1%drizzle}, sprinkle over the @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}.

Drain and rinse the @Cannellini Beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Pop a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle}.

Once hot, add the @Diced Chorizo{90%grams} and fry until slightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the cannellini beans, @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%grams}, @Chipotle Paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and the @Sugar{1%tsp} for the sauce.

Bring the chipotle chilli to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once the chilli has thickened, stir in the @Butter{20%grams} until melted.

Season with salt and pepper. Add a splash of @water{1%splash} if you feel it needs it.

Share the potato wedges between your serving bowls.

Top with the chorizo and bean chipotle chilli.

Drizzle over the @Soured Cream{75%grams} and sprinkle over the cheese to finish - wedges loaded!

Serve the @Wild Rocket{40%grams} leaves with a drizzle of @Balsamic Glaze{12%milliliters} on the side.

Enjoy!